# Phase 3.0.3: Timeline UI and Rendering Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (if subagents available) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Build a SwiftUI-based timeline UI with clip visualization, drag-to-reposition functionality, advanced snapping, and bidirectional video preview sync for multi-clip video editing.

**Architecture:** Hybrid SwiftUI approach using SwiftUI views for rendering with focused coordinator types for complex business logic (snapping, drag state machine, layout caching). Three-layer architecture: View Layer → Coordinator Layer → Data Layer.

**Tech Stack:** Swift 5.9, SwiftUI, @Observable framework, @MainActor, AVFoundation, Phase 3.0.1 models (VideoClip, ClipTrack), Phase 3.0.2 undo/redo system (ClipUndoManager, MoveClipOperation)

---

